To avoid the situation where support cases are submitted with contact addresses which are unmonitored, it was suggested by support that we could confirm the validity of the address when a case is submitted.

This is to avoid the situation documented here - http://extranet.atlassian.com/display/SUPPORT/2007/10/17/Support+requests+from+unmonitored+addresses

I guess one one way of doing this could be using the SMTP VRFY on the submitted address and confirming it is accepted. Of course, the administrator may want to submit an address that doesn't verify on the current server, so this should only be a warning.

